<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,640,1306]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis box="[199,434,1160,1185]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName box="[316,434,1160,1185]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Charybdis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hellerii">C. hellerii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is a non-indigenous portunid crab of Indo-West Pacific origin. The occurrence of this species in Bahia was first reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Carqueija" box="[603,937,1200,1226]" pageId="32" pageNumber="39" refString="Carqueija, C. R. G. &amp; Gouvea, E. P. (1996) A ocorrencia, na costa brasileira, de um Portunidae (Crustacea, Decapoda), originario do Indo-Pacifico e Mediterraneo. Nauplius, 4, 105 - 112." type="journal article" year="1996">
Carqueija &amp; Gouvêa (
<number box="[865,928,1200,1226]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, in Todos os Santos Bay. A further report, from Camamu Bay, was provided by 
<bibRefCitation box="[591,848,1240,1266]" pageId="32" pageNumber="38" refString="Almeida, A. O., Coelho, P. A. &amp; Santos, J. T. A. (2003) New records of decapod crustaceans (Dendrobranchiata and Brachyura) for the state of Bahia, Brazil. Nauplius, 11 (2), 129 - 133." type="journal article">
Almeida 
<emphasis box="[700,759,1240,1265]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[775,839,1240,1266]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. See 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezerra" box="[909,1224,1240,1266]" pageId="32" pageNumber="39" refString="Bezerra, L. E. A. &amp; Almeida, A. O. (2005) Primeiro registro da especie Indo-Pacifica Charybdis hellerii (A. Milne- Edwards, 1867) (Crustacea: Decapoda: Portunidae) para o litoral do Estado do Ceara. Tropical Oceanography, 33 (1), 33 - 38." type="journal article" year="2005">
Bezerra &amp; Almeida (
<number box="[1155,1217,1240,1266]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for a summary of the Brazilian records of 
<taxonomicName box="[434,552,1280,1305]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Charybdis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hellerii">
<emphasis box="[434,552,1280,1305]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">C. hellerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
